# NET-NEW under lead-loos (→ shopsystem-templates), Increment 1. Pins ADR-047 D3, the
# AUTHORING/DEV-TIME ADVISORY leg: "bin/system-manifest validate" compares the
# manifest-pinned tuple against the lead-5xnd baked image versions and WARNS on
# published-coherence drift but EXITS 0 (non-fatal). Advisory-first honors the lead
# author's authorship of the tuple (PDR-030 D4 rationale): a hard veto at authoring
# would invert authorship by letting a probe veto a deliberately-ahead-of-the-view pin.
# The BLOCKING counterpart fires only at adopter stand-up (scenarios 234/235).
#
# SCOPE: published-coherence vs lead-5xnd ONLY (the leg with a live data source on this
# host). Dependency-coherence vs lead-h2p0 is DESIGNED in ADR-047 D3 but has no data
# source until lead-h2p0 lands — NOT pinned here; the validator degrades to
# "published-coherence only" with an advisory note until then (deferred follow-up).
#
# @bc: and the reproducing @scenario_hash on dispatch are the Architect's; the
# block-only @scenario_hash below is the PO's authoring hash.
@lead_integration:templates
@scenario_hash:16a03e7e76772ad8
Scenario: "bin/system-manifest validate" warns on published-coherence drift between the manifest-pinned tuple and the lead-5xnd baked image versions but exits 0 at authoring/dev-time so a deliberately-ahead-of-the-view pin is not blocked
  Given a "lead" shop with the rendered ops command "bin/system-manifest" and a "system-manifest.yaml" whose "current:" release pins a "shopsystem-bc-launcher" version that differs from the "org.opencontainers.image.version" baked into the pulled bc-lead/bc-base image's lead-5xnd provenance
  When the operator runs "bin/system-manifest validate" at authoring/dev-time
  Then "bin/system-manifest validate" reports a published-coherence drift warning that names the incoherent component "shopsystem-bc-launcher", the manifest-pinned version, and the observed baked version it read from the image provenance
  And despite the reported drift the command exits with code 0, so the advisory warns loudly without blocking a deliberately-ahead-of-the-published-view pin
